<item>
            <title>[STORM-2496] Dependency artifacts should be uploaded to blobstore with READ permission for all</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STORM-2496</link>
                <project id="12314820" key="STORM">Apache Storm</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we submit topology via specific user with dependency artifacts, submitter uploads artifacts to the blobstore with user which runs the submission.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since uploaded artifacts are uploaded once and shared globally, other user might need to use uploaded artifact. (This is completely fine for non-secured cluster.) In this case, Supervisor fails to get artifact and crashes in result.&lt;/p&gt;

